VALUES
(44, 11, 8, 3, 11, 47, 47, 'nothing common or unclean', 'Clean and Unclean Distinction', 'This connection highlights the theme of distinguishing between clean and unclean. Acts 11:8 reflects Peter''s adherence to dietary laws, while Leviticus 11:47 establishes the criteria for these distinctions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 8, 15, 9, 11, 12, 'nothing common or unclean hath at any time entered into my mouth', 'Connection of Uncleanness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of uncleanness. In Acts, Peter refers to what is unclean, while Ezra describes the land as filled with uncleanness due to the people''s abominations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 8, 41, 7, 2, 2, 'nothing common or unclean', 'Clean and Unclean Foods', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of cleanliness in relation to food. Acts 11:8 reflects Peter''s objection to eating unclean things, while Mark 7:2 discusses the criticism of disciples for eating with unwashen hands, highlighting the Jewish purity laws.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 44, 15, 9, 9, NULL, 'Purification and Acceptance', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification and acceptance of all people. Both passages emphasize that God does not differentiate between groups, as seen in the cleansing and purifying of hearts.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 58, 9, 13, 14, 'What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common', 'Cleansing and Purification Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine cleansing in both passages. Acts 11:9 emphasizes what God has cleansed, while Hebrews 9:13-14 discusses the purifying power of Christ''s blood.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 44, 10, 15, 15, 'What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common', 'Connection of Divine Cleansing', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase, ''What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common,'' highlighting a divine declaration about purity. This repetition underscores the importance of God''s authority in defining what is clean.', 'quotation', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 44, 10, 28, 28, 'that call not thou common', 'God''s Cleansing of People', 'Both passages emphasize that God has declared certain individuals as clean, challenging Jewish customs regarding purity. This connection highlights the shift in understanding who is acceptable in God''s eyes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 44, 10, 34, 35, 'What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common', 'God''s Acceptance of All', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s acceptance of individuals regardless of their background. Both passages emphasize that what God has cleansed should not be considered common, indicating inclusivity in God''s acceptance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 9, 54, 4, 5, 5, 'What God hath cleansed', 'Sanctification and Cleansing', 'This connection highlights the theme of sanctification in both passages. Acts 11:9 speaks of what God has cleansed, while 1 Timothy 4:5 emphasizes that it is sanctified by the word of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 10, 4, 24, 10, 10, 'three times', 'Three Times of Blessing and Vision', 'This connection highlights the repetition of ''three times'' in both passages, emphasizing significant moments of divine intervention. In Acts, the vision is repeated three times, while in Numbers, Balaam blesses three times instead of cursing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 10, 43, 13, 38, 38, 'three times', 'Denial and Repetition Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of repetition in both passages. In Acts, the phrase ''three times'' indicates a significant repetition, while in John, Peter''s denial occurs ''thrice,'' emphasizing the importance of these repeated actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 10, 43, 21, 17, 17, 'this was done three times', 'Connection of Three Times', 'This connection highlights the repetition of ''three times'' in both passages, emphasizing significant moments in Peter''s experience. In Acts, the vision occurs three times, while in John, Jesus asks Peter three times about his love, indicating a theme of restoration and affirmation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 10, 47, 12, 8, 8, NULL, 'Repeated Appeals to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of repetition in seeking divine intervention. Both passages emphasize the act of calling upon God three times for a response or change.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 11, 2, 4, 14, 14, NULL, 'Divine Guidance and Meeting', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine guidance in both passages. In Acts, the arrival of the three men is a direct intervention from God, similar to how God directs Moses to meet Aaron, who is already on his way.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 11, 2, 4, 27, 27, NULL, 'Divine Guidance and Meeting', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine guidance leading to significant meetings. In both passages, God directs individuals to encounter others at pivotal moments.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 11, 44, 9, 10, 12, NULL, 'Divine Guidance in Visions', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine guidance through visions. Both passages describe individuals receiving specific instructions from the Lord, emphasizing the importance of obedience to God''s call.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 11, 44, 10, 17, 18, 'three men already come unto the house', 'Divine Guidance in Peter''s Journey', 'Both passages emphasize the arrival of men sent to Peter, highlighting the divine orchestration of events. The mention of ''three men'' in Acts 11:11 connects directly to the ''men which were sent from Cornelius'' in Acts 10:17-18, illustrating the unfolding of God''s plan.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 44, 8, 29, 29, 'the spirit bade me go', 'Guidance by the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the directive of the Spirit in guiding individuals to specific actions. In Acts 11:12, the Spirit instructs Peter to go without doubt, while in Acts 8:29, the Spirit directs Philip to approach the chariot.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 45, 3, 22, 22, 'nothing doubting', 'Faith and Acceptance', 'This connection highlights the theme of acceptance and belief. In Acts, the spirit guides Peter to accept Gentiles, while Romans emphasizes faith in Jesus Christ for all believers, indicating no distinction.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 44, 10, 23, 23, 'these six brethren accompanied me', 'Peter''s Journey with Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s decision to travel with certain brethren. In Acts 11:12, Peter mentions that ''these six brethren accompanied me,'' which directly connects to Acts 10:23 where he is described as being accompanied by ''certain brethren from Joppa.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 53, 2, 2, 2, 'the spirit bade me go', 'Connection of Spiritual Guidance', 'This connection highlights the theme of being guided by the spirit. In Acts, the spirit directs action without doubt, while in 2 Thessalonians, there is a caution against being troubled by misleading spiritual messages.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 40, 1, 20, 20, 'nothing doubting', 'Divine Guidance in Dreams', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine guidance through the Holy Spirit and angels. Both passages emphasize the importance of following divine instruction without doubt.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 43, 16, 13, 13, 'the spirit bade me go', 'Guidance of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in guiding believers. In Acts, the Spirit directs Peter to go without doubt, while in John, the Spirit of truth is promised to guide into all truth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 12, 66, 22, 17, 17, 'the spirit bade me go', 'Invitation by the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in inviting individuals to respond. In Acts, the Spirit guides Peter to go without doubt, while in Revelation, the Spirit invites all to come and take the water of life.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 13, 44, 10, 30, 32, 'Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon', 'Divine Instruction to Cornelius', 'Both passages emphasize the instruction given to Cornelius to send for Peter in Joppa. The angel''s message in Acts 10:30-32 directly leads to the account in Acts 11:13, where this event is recounted.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 13, 44, 9, 43, 43, 'Simon, whose surname is Peter', 'Connection through Peter in Joppa', 'Both passages emphasize Simon Peter''s presence in Joppa. The mention of Peter in Acts 11:13 connects directly to his stay with Simon the tanner in Acts 9:43.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 13, 44, 10, 3, 6, 'Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon', 'Angel''s Message to Cornelius', 'Both passages emphasize the angel''s instruction to send men to Joppa for Peter. This connection highlights the divine guidance in Cornelius''s vision and Peter''s subsequent role in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 13, 44, 12, 11, 11, 'an angel in his house', 'Angelic Intervention in Deliverance', 'This connection highlights the role of angels in guiding and delivering key figures in the early church. Both passages emphasize the presence of an angel and the subsequent actions taken by Peter in response to divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 13, 58, 1, 14, 14, 'an angel in his house', 'Angelic Messengers in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the role of angels as messengers in both passages. In Acts, an angel instructs Cornelius to seek Peter, while Hebrews describes angels as ministering spirits sent to aid believers.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 44, 10, 22, 22, 'words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved', 'Connection of Salvation Messages', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing words that lead to salvation. Acts 11:14 speaks of words that will save, while Acts 10:22 mentions hearing words from Peter, which are implied to be salvific.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
